# Privacy Policy — TimeTiles

**Last updated: April 2026**

## Overview

TimeTiles is a Chrome extension that displays live clocks for configured office locations and provides time zone conversion tools. This policy explains how the extension handles your data.

## Data Collected

TimeTiles stores the following data **locally in your browser only**:

- Any custom locations you add to the "My locations" section (city name and timezone)

No other data is stored. Office tile times are calculated on the fly from your system clock and are never saved.

## Location Data

TimeTiles requests access to your browser's geolocation in order to:

- Detect which office you are nearest to
- Show a "Your location" tile with your local time

Your location coordinates are used only in memory to render the tiles and are never stored or transmitted anywhere. If you decline the location permission, the extension falls back to matching your system timezone instead.

## Data Storage

Custom saved locations are stored using Chrome's `storage.local` API. This data never leaves your browser and is not accessible to any website or third party.

## Data Sharing

No data is collected, transmitted, or shared with any external server, service, or third party.

## Permissions

- **storage** - used to save your custom locations locally
- **sidePanel** - used to display the extension in Chrome's side panel
- **geolocation** - used to detect your location for nearest-office highlighting; coordinates are never stored or transmitted

